Package core

Interface HlaPayload

  • All Superinterfaces:
    HlaDynamicalEntityAttributes, HlaHLAobjectRootAttributes, HlaObjectInstanceBase, HlaPayloadAttributes, HlaPhysicalEntityAttributes
    public interface HlaPayload
extends HlaPayloadAttributes, HlaObjectInstanceBase
    Interface used to represent an object instance.

    This class is ThreadSafe as defined by Java Concurrency in Practice, see jcip.net.

      • addHlaPayloadListener

        void addHlaPayloadListener​(HlaPayloadListener listener)
        Adds a listener. The listener is notified when any attribute of this object is updated. This listener is also called when an interaction is sent to this object. This method is idempotent. To make sure that no attribute updates arrive before adding the listener, use: HlaPayloadManager.addHlaPayloadDefaultInstanceListener(HlaPayloadListener listener).
        Parameters:
        listener - The listener to add.

      • removeHlaPayloadListener

        void removeHlaPayloadListener​(HlaPayloadListener listener)
        Removes a listener. This method is idempotent. Trying to remove a non-registered listener is equivalent to a no-op.
        Parameters:
        listener - The listener to remove.

      • addHlaPayloadValueListener

        void addHlaPayloadValueListener​(HlaPayloadValueListener valueListener)
        Adds a valueListener. The valueListener is notified when any attribute of this object is updated. Note that the attribute values that are notified are not guaranteed to be the latest available values for that attribute. This method is idempotent. To make sure that no attribute updates arrive before adding the listener, use: HlaPayloadManager.addHlaPayloadDefaultInstanceValueListener(HlaPayloadValueListener valueListener).
        Parameters:
        valueListener - The valueListener to add.

      • removeHlaPayloadValueListener

        void removeHlaPayloadValueListener​(HlaPayloadValueListener valueListener)
        Removes a valueListener. This method is idempotent. Trying to remove a non-registered valueListener is equivalent to a no-op.
        Parameters:
        valueListener - The valueListener to remove.
